race.description: Werris Creek Cup Country Boosted Bm 66 Handicap
race.comment: INVINCIBLE RED (3) just missed in a similar race to this at Tamworth two runs back then struggled in a BM82 at Scone last start. In a more suitable race today and the engagement of Aaron Bullock is a positive move. It has been three years since SEMECO (9) won his only race but his form of late has been strong. Battled on well to just miss the frame last time out in a Class 2 over this distance at Moree. Drops 5kgs today after the claim and won't spend a cent from the nice draw. AWESOME TYCOON (4) appreciated the drop in grade when a closing second over 1400m at Coonabarabran recently. Is a winner at the mile and should be peaking now after three runs back from a spell. SANZENO (8) led and gave a kick but was edged out last start in a Class 3 over the mile at Coonabarabran. Has hit form after three runs back and will be at his peak for this. MARNOO (7) did a good job to score at Moree over this journey last time and is right in contention again.
